                "transcript":"<p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left; font-size: 110%; font-weight: bold\">Closing out Temporary Accounts</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Suppose a company had the following revenues and expenses during the year.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Timeline with Revenues above and Expenses below. Revenues of $1,000, $800, $500, $900 are marked above the timeline. Expenses of $2,000, $100, and $500 are marked below the timeline.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Totals for this year: Revenues ($3,200) minus Expenses ($3,600) = Net Income ($600).</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">At the end of the accounting period, the company closes out the Revenue and Expense accounts on the income statement, so they start with a zero balance at the beginning of the new accounting period.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Timeline fades out and previous Revenues and Expenses are wiped out showing only $0 for each.] </p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Balance sheet appears with Assets = $5,000, Liabilities = $4,000, Owners’ Equity = $1,000.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Then the company adds the net income from the income statement to its Owners’ Equity account on the balance sheet.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">The $600 in net income increases Owners’ Equity by $600. </p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Owners’ Equity on the balance sheet increases to $1,600.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">To keep the equation in balance, total assets and/or liabilities also change. For simplicity, we’ll say that our company’s assets increase by $600.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Assets on the balances sheet increase to $5,600.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">After closing out the temporary accounts (income statement) to the permanent accounts (balance sheet), the operating cycle begins anew with the next accounting period.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[Timeline returns with both ends labeled with Balance Sheet on top and December 31 on the bottom. The middle of the timeline is labeled as Income Statement with arrows pointing to both ends. The timeline moves to the left off screen. A new timeline with the same labels moves on screen from the right.]</p>"
