                "transcript": "<p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left; font-size: 110%; font-weight: bold\">Cash Flow Example</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Last year, the Origami Life Insurance Company received $10 million in premium income and paid $8 million in contractual benefits.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[An office building appears. “$10,000,000” flows into the building, and “8,000,000” comes out the other side.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Origami’s cash flow statement therefore includes a $2 million net cash inflow from operating activities.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Operating Activities:</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$10,000,000 - $8,000,000 = $2,000,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">The company also sold $150,000 of bonds from its asset portfolio and purchased $160,000 in mortgages.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[A bond certificate for $150,000 flows into the building, and a contract with $160,000 on it flows out.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">The cash flow statement includes a $10,000 net cash outflow from investing activities.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Investing Activities:</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$150,000 - $160,000 = -$10,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Last, Origami paid $50,000 in cash dividends to stockholders during 2018.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[A money bag labeled “$50,000 Cash Dividends” flows out of the building.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">So, Origami’s cash flow statement includes a $50,000 net cash outflow from financing activities.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">[The office building fades out.]</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Financing Activities:</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$0 - $50,000 = -$50,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Cash Flow from Operating Activities: $2,000,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Cash Flow from Investing Activities: -$10,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Cash Flow from Financing Activities: -$50,000.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Cash Flow from All Activities: $1,940,000.</p>"
