				"label": "12.3: Policyowner Service Function Responsibilities",
				"video_url": "http://ry6g4c.cloud.influxis.com/ManagedContent/361_Video12-3_h264_baseline_l31_3500k_720p_aac_96k.mp4",
                "transcript": "<p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left; font-size:110%;\"><strong>Policyowner Service Function Responsibilities</strong></p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><em>Start with a replication of the org chart Figure 12.2 on pg. 12.13; the shaded boxes start clear but will be filled in with color as we go. </em></p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><img src=\"includes/images/libraryvids/12.3_html_m7acd3bd0.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:100%;\"/></p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Brindle&rsquo;s senior vice president of policyowner service is responsible for both the East and West divisions of the policyowner service function.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">The assistant vice president of each division is responsible for five service departments. Each service department has a manager who is directly responsible for the department.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Policyowner Service is a cost center; its responsibility report includes only costs. The responsibility report for each organizational level includes the cost of each responsibility below it.</p><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">For example, the total costs of the West Division&rsquo;s Reinstatements cost center&hellip;</p><table border=\"1\" width=\"479\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"7\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"104\">&nbsp;</td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Actual</strong></p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Budget</strong></p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Variance</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"104\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Total direct costs</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$28,263</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$24,625</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$3,638</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"104\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Indirect costs</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">8,014</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">8,200</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">(186)</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"104\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Total costs</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">36,277</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">32,825</p></td><td width=\"106\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">3,452</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">appear on the responsibility report for the West Division.</p><table border=\"1\" width=\"614\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"7\"><tbody><tr><td width=\"167\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Direct Departmental Costs</p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Actual</strong></p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Budget</strong></p></td><td width=\"129\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\"><strong>Variance</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"167\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Coverage changes</p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$28,263</p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$24,625</p></td><td width=\"129\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">$3,638</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"167\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Reinstatements</p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">36,277</p></td><td width=\"130\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">32,825</p></td><td width=\"129\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">3,452</p></td></tr><tr><td width=\"167\"><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">Policy values</p></td><td width=\"130\">&nbsp;</td><td width=\"130\">&nbsp;</td><td width=\"129\">&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"width: 100%; text-align:left;\">The costs for the West Division appear on the responsibility report for the Policyowner Service function, and so on.</p>"
